# 🧾 Invoice Agent

A lightweight Node.js backend for creating, scheduling, and sending invoices via email. This is an AI Invoice Agent that creates scheduled draft invoices (weekly or monthly), lets you edit them before sending, and sends them via email with a PDF attachment.

## Features

- ✅ **Draft Invoice System** - Create draft invoices that require approval before sending
- 📅 **Recurring Invoices** - Automatic weekly (Mondays) or monthly (1st of month) draft creation
- 📝 **Edit Before Send** - Review and modify invoices before emailing
- 📧 **Email with PDF** - Professional PDF attachment with styled HTML email
- 💰 **Payment Tracking** - Mark invoices as paid with payment details
- ⏰ **Payment Reminders** - Identify and send reminders for overdue invoices
- 📁 **JSON Storage** - Simple file-based storage, no database required

## Tech Stack

- **Node.js** - Runtime
- **Express.js** - Web framework
- **pdfkit** - PDF generation
- **nodemailer** - Email sending
- **node-cron** - Scheduling
- **uuid** - Unique ID generation

## Quick Start

### 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
cd invoice-agent
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Email (Optional)

Create a `.env` file or set environment variables:

```bash
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
SMTP_FROM="Your Business <invoices@yourdomain.com>"
```

> **Note:** Without email configuration, the system will log emails to the console instead of sending them. Perfect for development!

### 3. Start the Server

```bash
npm start
```

Server runs at: http://localhost:3000

### 4. Load Sample Data (Optional)

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/load-sample-data
```

## API Endpoints

### Customers

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/customers` | List all customers |
| POST | `/customers` | Create a new customer |
| PUT | `/customers/:id` | Update a customer |

**Create Customer Example:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/customers \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "address": "123 Main St, City, State 12345",
    "recurringType": "monthly",
    "recurringItems": [
      {"description": "Monthly Service", "quantity": 1, "price": 99.99}
    ]
  }'
```

### Draft Invoices

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/drafts` | List all draft invoices |
| GET | `/drafts/:id` | Get a specific draft |
| POST | `/drafts` | Create a new draft invoice |
| PUT | `/drafts/:id` | Edit a draft invoice |
| DELETE | `/drafts/:id` | Delete a draft invoice |
| POST | `/drafts/:id/send` | Approve and send via email |

**Create Draft Example:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/drafts \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "customerId": "cust-001",
    "items": [
      {"description": "Web Development", "quantity": 10, "price": 100.00},
      {"description": "Design Work", "quantity": 5, "price": 75.00}
    ],
    "dueDate": "2024-02-15",
    "notes": "Project Phase 1"
  }'
```

**Edit Draft Example:**
```bash
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/drafts/draft-001 \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "items": [
      {"description": "Updated Service", "quantity": 2, "price": 150.00}
    ],
    "notes": "Revised invoice"
  }'
```

**Send Invoice:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/drafts/draft-001/send
```

### Sent Invoices

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/invoices` | List all sent invoices |
| GET | `/invoices/:id` | Get a specific invoice |
| POST | `/invoices/:id/mark-paid` | Mark invoice as paid |

**Mark as Paid Example:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/invoices/inv-001/mark-paid \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "paymentMethod": "Bank Transfer",
    "paymentReference": "TXN-123456"
  }'
```

### Payment Reminders

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/reminders` | List unpaid invoices needing reminders |
| POST | `/invoices/:id/send-reminder` | Send payment reminder email |

**Check Reminders:**
```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/reminders
```

**Send Reminder:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/invoices/inv-002/send-reminder
```

## Invoice PDF Layout

Generated PDFs include:
- 📋 **Header** - Invoice number, date, due date
- 👤 **Customer Info Box** - Name, email, address
- 📊 **Items Table** - Description, quantity, unit price, line total
- 💵 **Totals Section** - Subtotal, total (highlighted)
- 🔤 **Amount in Words** - e.g., "Six Hundred Ninety-Eight Dollars and Ninety Cents Only"
- 🏦 **Bank Details** - Payment information
- 📝 **Notes** - Any additional notes

## Recurring Invoice Schedules

Configure customers with `recurringType`:

- **`weekly`** - Drafts created every Monday
- **`monthly`** - Drafts created on the 1st of each month
- **`null`** - No automatic invoices

The scheduler runs daily at midnight and creates **draft invoices only**. You must manually review and send them.

## File Structure

```
invoice-agent/
├── server.js              # Main Express server & API routes
├── invoiceGenerator.js    # PDF generation with pdfkit
├── emailService.js        # Email sending with nodemailer
├── scheduler.js           # Cron job for recurring invoices
├── package.json           # Dependencies
├── sample-data.json       # Sample data for testing
├── data/
│   ├── customers.json     # Customer storage
│   ├── drafts.json        # Draft invoices storage
│   └── invoices.json      # Sent invoices storage
└── pdfs/                  # Temporary PDF storage (auto-created)
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `PORT` | Server port | 3000 |
| `SMTP_HOST` | SMTP server hostname | - |
| `SMTP_PORT` | SMTP server port | 587 |
| `SMTP_USER` | SMTP username | - |
| `SMTP_PASS` | SMTP password | - |
| `SMTP_FROM` | From email address | invoices@example.com |
| `TZ` | Timezone for scheduler | America/New_York |

## Workflow

1. **Setup Customers** - Add customers with optional recurring schedules
2. **Automatic Drafts** - Scheduler creates drafts based on schedules
3. **Review & Edit** - Use `GET /drafts` to view, `PUT /drafts/:id` to edit
4. **Send Invoice** - Use `POST /drafts/:id/send` to email with PDF
5. **Track Payment** - Use `POST /invoices/:id/mark-paid` when paid
6. **Send Reminders** - Check `GET /reminders` and send as needed

## Example Workflow

```bash
# 1. Load sample data
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/load-sample-data

# 2. View all drafts
curl http://localhost:3000/drafts

# 3. Edit a draft
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/drafts/draft-001 \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"notes": "Updated notes for this invoice"}'

# 4. Send the invoice
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/drafts/draft-001/send

# 5. View sent invoices
curl http://localhost:3000/invoices

# 6. Mark as paid
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/invoices/draft-001/mark-paid \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"paymentMethod": "Credit Card"}'
```

